remarks: If ` A ` and ` B ` are members of a Tarski class, their unordered pair is also an element of the class.  JFM CLASSES2 th. 3 (partly).  (Contributed by FL, 22-Feb-2011.)  (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 20-Jun-2013.)
statement: tskpr $p |- ( ( T e. Tarski /\ A e. T /\ B e. T ) -> { A , B } e. T ) $.
